data.enText: to make sb unable to hear the sounds around them because there is too much noise

data.chText: 汽笛声震得她耳朵都快聋了。
data.enText: The noise of the siren was deafening her.

value.def: If a noise deafens you, it is so loud that you cannot hear anything else at the same time.

example.ex: The noise of the typewriters deafened her.
example.tran: 打字机的噪声吵得她什么都听不见。

value.tran: 震（或吵）得…听不见其他声音

value.def: If you are deafened by something, you are made deaf by it, or are unable to hear for some time.

example.ex: He was deafened by the noise from the gun.
